<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1444.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 2731, of the 9th ultimo, and to approve your note to the Tsung-li
                            Yamên, of the same date, protesting against the exclusion of Chinese
                            converts to Christianity from entering Chinese Government
                            examinations.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>